gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 123, Jazz 95
gameRecap.excerpt: The Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the Utah Jazz, 123-95 tonight in Minnesota. Anthony Edwards finished with a team-high 31 points along with eight rebounds and six assists for the Timberwolves, while Karl-Anthony Towns tallied 25 points, seven rebounds and two steals in the game. Lauri Markkanen recorded 22 points, eight rebounds and four three pointers. The Timberwolves improve their record to 3-2 with the win, while the Jazz fall to 2-5 for the season.
